Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.64,0:02:16.01,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在我们的行星之间\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Among our planets,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.04,0:02:19.65,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,冥王星一直都比较特别 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Pluto was long considered To be a bit different,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.68,0:02:21.48,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,比其他的行星小很多 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Much smaller than the rest.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.52,0:02:25.55,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,按自身大小比例算来 它却已有最大的卫星 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It has the largest moon In proportion to its own size.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.39,0:02:31.39,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它的公转轨道也是最倾斜和最椭圆 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It also has the most inclined And eccentric orbit.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.99,0:02:37.30,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它的轨道形状有点像鸡蛋 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Its orbit Is sort of shaped like an egg.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.33,0:02:40.63,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它的轨道有的地方靠太阳很近 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Pluto's orbit causes it to get Significantly closer to the sun
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.67,0:02:42.84,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,有的地方离太阳又很远 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And then further away From the sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.44,0:02:45.57,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,浩瀚宇宙中的这个小星球 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This cosmic needle In a haystack
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.61,0:02:48.71,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,躲避天文学家的搜捕已有好几十年 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Eluded planet hunters For decades.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.94,0:02:54.11,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,第八颗行星海王星发现于1846 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The eighth planet, Neptune, Had been discovered in 1846,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.15,0:02:57.22,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在19世纪末期 天文学家相信\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And astronomers at the turn Of the century were convinced
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.25,0:02:58.62,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,还有第九颗行星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}There was a ninth planet
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.65,0:03:02.42,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在太阳系的远处 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In the far reaches Of our solar system.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.79,0:03:09.83,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,帕西瓦尔·罗威尔启动了搜寻冥王星计划 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The search for pluto Was started by Percival Lowell
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.86,0:03:12.07,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在罗威尔天文台 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}At Lowell Observatory.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.10,0:03:13.80,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他认为那里有个X行星 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}He thought there was A planet x there
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.83,0:03:18.00,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因为X行星扰乱了天王星和海王星的轨道 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That was perturbing the orbits Of Uranus and Neptune.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.01,0:03:20.24,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在找到X行星之前 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Before finding The elusive planet,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.27,0:03:22.98,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,罗威尔就辞世了 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Lowell passed away.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.01,0:03:26.45,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是天文台的研究助手克莱德·汤博\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But the observatory's Research assistant, Clyde Tombaugh
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.48,0:03:28.72,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,继续了他的搜寻 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Continued his quest.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.75,0:03:32.82,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在1930年他24岁那年 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In 1930 at the age of 24,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.85,0:03:35.62,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,汤博捕捉到一个星球的图像 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Tombaugh captured an image Of an object
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.66,0:03:39.69,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,似乎验证了罗威尔的预言 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That seemed to validate Lowell's predictions.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.73,0:03:42.06,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他向全世界宣布了这个发现 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The discovery Was announced to the world
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.10,0:03:46.97,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这个星球被正式取名为"冥王星" \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And the object Was given an official name-- "Pluto."
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.00,0:03:50.57,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但它是不是X行星呢？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But was Pluto planet x?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.60,0:03:54.07,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一些科学家认为冥王星太小 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Some scientists argued That Pluto was far too small
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.11,0:03:56.28,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,质量不够大 不能明显地\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And didn't have enough mass To significantly
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.31,0:03:59.25,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,扰乱它附近行星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Perturb the orbits Of its neighboring gas giants,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.28,0:04:01.95,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,天王星和海王星的轨道 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Uranus and Neptune.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.98,0:04:03.65,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,后来天文学家意识到\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Astronomers have since realized
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.68,0:04:06.75,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,根本没有X行星存在 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That there is no such planet x.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.79,0:04:07.72,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,X行星的预测\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It had been predicted
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.75,0:04:11.79,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,错误的估计了海王星的质量 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Using inaccurate estimates Of Neptune's mass.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.23,0:04:16.63,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,即使冥王星不是X行星 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Even though Pluto Wasn't planet x,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.66,0:04:20.33,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它是否有资格列为行星之列呢？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Could it still be classified As a planet?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.77,0:04:25.10,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,起初"行星"这个词只代表"天上运转的星体" \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The first term for planet Just meant "wanderer In the sky."
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.14,0:04:27.84,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,行星只是与恒星相对的运动的星体 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It was the things that moved Relative to the stars.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.87,0:04:29.51,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以对古希腊人来说\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So, to the ancient greeks,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.54,0:04:30.48,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,月亮是行星 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The Moon was a planet,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.51,0:04:31.61,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,太阳是行星 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The Sun was a planet,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.65,0:04:33.92,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,地球不是行星 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The Earth was not.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.85,0:04:37.88,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,当然现在我们知道地球\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Of course, When we realized that the Earth
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.92,0:04:40.35,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,实际是绕着太阳运动 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Is actually going around the Sun
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.89,0:04:43.82,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,月亮绕着地球运动 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And that the Moon Is going around the Earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.86,0:04:46.03,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,行星的定义开始改变 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The definition of planet Changed again.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.06,0:04:47.73,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,地球成了行星 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Earth became a planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.76,0:04:49.40,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,而太阳和月亮就不算行星了 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The Sun and the Moon Were taken away
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.43,0:04:51.16,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,当时还有6颗行星 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And there were Finally six.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.20,0:04:54.03,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,后来发现了天王星 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And over time, Uranus was discovered.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.07,0:04:55.57,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,发现了海王星 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Neptune was discovered,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.60,0:04:59.37,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以行星就有了7颗 8颗 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So there were--there were seven, There were eight.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.81,0:05:03.04,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,尽管冥王星后来被证明比月球要小 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Although it later proved To be smaller than our Moon,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.08,0:05:06.65,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但原以为冥王星与火星一般大小 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Pluto was originally thought To be as large as Mars.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.18,0:05:09.95,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,于是汤博发现的冥王星被认定为\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So tombaugh's discovery Was anointed
