Dialogue: 0,0:37:12.87,0:37:16.08,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,大到足够能把我们地球放进黑斑中心 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Large enough for our Earth To fit in the center,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:16.11,0:37:20.75,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这风暴类似与木星上声名狼藉的大红斑 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The storm resembled Jupiter's infamous Great red spot.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:23.28,0:37:26.72,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,大红斑是一块巨大的反气旋 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The great red spot Is a huge anticyclone,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:26.75,0:37:30.62,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它由许多较小的风暴组成 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Which is fed By many smaller storms That keeps it alive, If you like.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:31.46,0:37:34.19,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,否则它会驱散消失\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Otherwise it would dissipate And disappear.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:34.83,0:37:36.20,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,以大黑斑看来 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In the case Of the great dark spot,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:36.23,0:37:39.03,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们相信大气中会是相当的动乱 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We believe It's more of an instability In the atmosphere,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:39.07,0:37:44.87,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,风暴涌入高速的大气层中 使得大气来回翻滚 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Which rocks back and forth Because of the flows In that very fast atmosphere.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:47.81,0:37:50.91,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,恰在第一次发现大黑斑的5年后 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Just five years After the spot Was first discovered,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:51.11,0:37:53.82,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,科学家们再次大吃一惊 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Scientist were in for another surprise
Dialogue: 0,0:37:55.32,0:37:56.72,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,哈勃太空望远镜\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The Hubble Space Telescope
Dialogue: 0,0:37:56.75,0:37:59.75,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,对准海王星 发现\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Turned its eye toward Neptune Only to see
Dialogue: 0,0:37:59.79,0:38:03.66,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,海王星上最大的风暴消失了 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That the largest storm On the planet was gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:11.48,0:38:15.08,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,海王星的大黑斑发生什么事了？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}What happened To Neptune's great dark spot?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:16.91,0:38:19.05,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,5年时间内\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Within a span of five years,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:19.08,0:38:20.85,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,该行星上最大的风暴\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The largest storm on the planet
Dialogue: 0,0:38:20.89,0:38:24.46,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,从南半球就这么轻易的消失了 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Simply vanished From the southern hemisphere.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:26.99,0:38:30.96,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但这并不意味着海王星上所有风暴都停止了 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But that didn't mean the end Of mega storms on Neptune.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:32.00,0:38:35.06,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,天文学家使用哈勃太空望远镜观测到\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Astronomers using the Hubble Space Telescope observed
Dialogue: 0,0:38:35.10,0:38:38.04,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一块新的大黑斑出现了 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That a new great dark spot Had appeared.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:39.27,0:38:42.67,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但这次黑斑出现在行星的北半球 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But this time, in the planet's Northern hemisphere.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:43.67,0:38:46.21,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,似乎海王星上\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It seems that on Neptune,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:46.24,0:38:48.65,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,风暴系统出现在大斑迹之处 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The storm systems that manifest As these big spots,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:48.68,0:38:50.75,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,利用望远镜或飞行器你可以看得到 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}You can see, With a spacecraft or telescope.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:50.78,0:38:53.28,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,相比之下 它们有点来去匆忙 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They sort of come and go On shorter time scales Than,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:53.31,0:38:55.18,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,比如说木星上的大红斑\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}say, The great red spot on Jupiter
Dialogue: 0,0:38:55.22,0:38:58.12,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,已存在那里好几百年了 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Which has been there For hundreds of years.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:58.82,0:39:01.59,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这些风暴系统不仅短暂\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Not only are these Storm systems transient,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:01.63,0:39:03.73,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,而且古怪 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They are also eccentric.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:06.36,0:39:09.13,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,科学家发现大黑斑的大小\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Scientists observed That the size Of the great dark spot
Dialogue: 0,0:39:09.17,0:39:11.53,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,振荡漂移了几千平方英里 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Oscillated by several thousand Square miles
Dialogue: 0,0:39:11.57,0:39:14.84,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在仅仅8天之内\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}within a span Of just eight days.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:18.18,0:39:22.41,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,消失 再现 完全奇异的移动 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The disappearance And reappearance And overall erratic movement
Dialogue: 0,0:39:22.45,0:39:24.28,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,使得海王星的暴风系统\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Make Neptune's storm systems
Dialogue: 0,0:39:24.31,0:39:28.12,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,成为太阳系中最难以预知的风暴之一 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Some of the most unpredictable In the solar system.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:32.49,0:39:34.96,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,类似于其它外太行星邻居 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Similar to its Outer planet neighbors,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:34.99,0:39:38.23,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,海王星也有复杂的卫星体系 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Neptune has A complex system of moons.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:39.66,0:39:42.70,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,目前已发现13颗卫星 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Thirteen have been discovered So far.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:48.54,0:39:49.87,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,海王星的一些卫星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Some of Neptune's moons
Dialogue: 0,0:39:49.91,0:39:53.88,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,可能起源形成于太阳系的其他地方 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}May have originally formed Elsewhere in the solar system.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:56.78,0:39:58.11,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,海王星捕获的这些卫星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Neptune is probably Capturing these moons
Dialogue: 0,0:39:58.15,0:40:00.18,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,可能来自于太阳系中\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}From the vast amount of material That's actually
Dialogue: 0,0:40:00.22,0:40:03.45,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,海王星和冥王星之外的大量物质 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In our solar system Beyond the orbit Of Neptune and Pluto.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:03.49,0:40:06.56,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,外太空有许多冰星体\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}There is a lot Of very icy bodies,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:06.59,0:40:09.63,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,小行星体和其他岩类物质 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Small bodies, planetesimals And other rocky things
Dialogue: 0,0:40:09.66,0:40:13.16,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,穿行于太阳系碎片之间 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That pass through Our solar system And other debris.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:14.20,0:40:15.03,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,偶尔\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Every so often,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:15.07,0:40:17.67,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一些碎片可能会互相撞击 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Some of this debris Might collide with each other
Dialogue: 0,0:40:17.70,0:40:20.94,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这时碎片就可能被撞进太阳系 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And then they get pushed in Towards the solar system.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:20.97,0:40:24.91,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,有的冰冻碎片最后形成了彗星 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Some of these icy bodies End up as comets.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:24.94,0:40:27.04,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但如果碎片被撞向特定的方向 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But if one is pushed In the right direction
Dialogue: 0,0:40:27.08,0:40:28.75,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,被撞在特定的时刻 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}At the right time,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:28.78,0:40:32.35,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那么这一碎片就有可能被行星的引力吸住 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It can be captured by a planet's Gravitational pull,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:32.38,0:40:35.15,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,变成一颗卫星 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Becoming a moon.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:37.89,0:40:40.16,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,海王星最大的卫星海卫一\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Neptune's largest moon, Triton,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:40.19,0:40:43.29,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,大小与月亮相当 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Is roughly the size Of Earth's moon.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:43.93,0:40:48.87,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它是太阳系中现已知的最冷的星球 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It is the coldest object In our solar system, Ever observed by astronomers
Dialogue: 0,0:40:48.90,0:40:52.27,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,甚至比冥王星还要冷 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Even more frigid than Pluto.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:52.67,0:40:54.54,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,只有绝对零度以上40度 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Only 40 degrees Above absolute zero,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:54.57,0:40:56.14,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,大约-390华氏度 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}About minus 390 degrees fahrenheit.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:56.17,0:41:00.61,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如此之冷以至于通常呈气态的氮气\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So cold that the nitrogen Which would normally be In a gaseous form,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:00.64,0:41:04.21,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,都成了冰态覆盖在极地区 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Forms an icy polar cap On this moon.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:04.75,0:41:09.59,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,海卫一如此冷主要是因为它的表面反光性太好 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Triton is so cold Primarily because the surface Is so reflective.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:09.62,0:41:12.97,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,照在它表面光约有70%\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}About 70 percent of the light That hits the surface of Triton
Dialogue: 0,0:41:12.99,0:41:14.19,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,都反射了出去 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Is reflected back.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:14.22,0:41:17.36,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以海卫一吸收不到太多的太阳能 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And with that much light Not being absorbed By the planet,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:17.39,0:41:19.70,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,变得非常非常的冷 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It just gets very, very cold.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:22.03,0:41:25.03,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,海卫一的组成成分与冥王星相似\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Triton, it could well Be similar in composition To Pluto.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:25.07,0:41:27.24,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,表面是冰雪覆盖 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We see ices On the surface there.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:27.27,0:41:28.04,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在海卫一表面\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}One of the fascinating things
Dialogue: 0,0:41:28.07,0:41:30.57,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,有一件奇妙的景观 羽毛状的烟云\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That we see on the surface Of triton are actually plumes,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:30.61,0:41:33.01,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,火山上空的烟云 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Essentially volcanoes.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:33.01,0:41:33.71,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们来看看这些火山 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And we see these plumes,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:33.74,0:41:36.01,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,当航天器经过海王星和海卫一的时候 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We've actually seen them Coming out in real time
Dialogue: 0,0:41:36.05,0:41:40.28,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们可以看到火山的实时喷发 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}With the Voyager spacecraft When it went past Neptune and Triton.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:40.28,0:41:42.12,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不像地球上的火山 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Unlike Earth's volcanoes,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:42.15,0:41:43.92,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,海卫一喷泉似的火山爆发\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Triton's geyser-like eruptions
Dialogue: 0,0:41:43.95,0:41:49.56,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,喷出大量混合液 包含液氮 液态甲烷 氨水\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Spew a mixture Of liquid nitrogen, methane, And ammonia.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:51.39,0:41:53.80,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,并且喷出后的混合液\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And an upsurge instantly freezes
Dialogue: 0,0:41:53.83,0:41:58.50,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,飞上5英里高的大气中马上就结冰了 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}As it rockets five miles high Into its thin atmosphere.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:59.14,0:42:00.07,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一旦到了空中\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Once airborne,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:00.10,0:42:03.98,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在冰粒落下之前 冰粒将会被大气中的风带走\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The ice can be carried Along for miles by winds In the atmosphere
Dialogue: 0,0:42:04.14,0:42:07.25,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,带走好几英里 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}before snowing Back down onto the surface.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:14.75,0:42:17.75,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,海卫一上的这些地质活动引发了科学家的思考 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Geological activity on triton Makes scientists wonder
Dialogue: 0,0:42:17.79,0:42:22.79,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在海卫一冰雪覆盖的地表之下 如果有水的存在呢？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}If there's water, Perhaps being heated Under Triton's Icy exterior
Dialogue: 0,0:42:24.93,0:42:26.46,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,按照这一理论\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And as the theory goes,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:26.50,0:42:29.60,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,有水的地方就会有生命 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Where there's water, Life could be present.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:32.14,0:42:33.40,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如果有水的话\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}If that's the case,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:33.44,0:42:35.84,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,海王星的最大的这颗卫星可能成为\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Neptune's largest moon Could be home to
Dialogue: 0,0:42:35.87,0:42:39.64,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,空前的最大发现之一 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}one Of the biggest discoveries Of all time.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:49.15,0:42:51.42,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但由于计划和时间关系 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But due to planning And transit times,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:51.45,0:42:53.82,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在飞行器抵达天王星和海王星之前\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It will be at least two decades
Dialogue: 0,0:42:53.86,0:42:56.86,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,至少还要等20年 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Before we approach Uranus or Neptune again.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:58.30,0:43:00.96,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们有讨论 但目前还没有方案 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We've had discussions But there are no current plans.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:01.00,0:43:01.90,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,利用飞行器我们可以\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We could, with Voyager,
